# Supabase client configuration for the Supplier Sustainability Portal (v2.0).
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` for local development and fill in the values
# from Supabase: Project Settings -> API. The same two variables must be set
# in Netlify (Site configuration -> Environment variables) for the deploy.
#
# Both are VITE_-prefixed, so Vite inlines them into the client bundle — this
# is intended. The anon key is safe to expose because RLS restricts the anon
# role to insert-only with no read. Never commit real values: `.env.local` is
# gitignored, and only this names-only example is tracked.

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
